note.p:
Martin B. H. Weiss and Michael B. Spring, Selected Intellectual Property Issues in Standardization, Department of Information Science, University of Pittsburgh, Pittsburgh PA 15260, September 1992, and presented at the Twentieth Annual Telecommunications Policy Research Conference, Solomons, MD, September 12–14, 1992, p 1. The paper (at
http://www2.sis.pitt.edu/~spring/papers/stdip1.pdf
) argues convincingly that the nature of anticipatory standards has an impact on the nature of IPR in standardization. (footnote in original text)
